module terok_socket 1.1;

# Legacy ``terok_socket_t`` socket type ‚Äî kept for service-side
# fallback only.
#
# Background.  Pre-hardening, all terok service sockets carried a
# single shared type ``terok_socket_t`` and a single broad
# ``container_t connectto terok_socket_t`` allow rule was the only
# thing that let rootless Podman containers reach gate / vault /
# ssh-agent.  The optional hardening modules (``terok_gate``,
# ``terok_vault``) replaced that with **per-service socket types**
# (``terok_gate_sock_t``, ``terok_vault_sock_t``,
# ``terok_vault_ssh_sock_t``) ‚Äî services apply them via
# ``setsockcreatecon`` at bind time; container connectto is granted
# per-type by the per-service modules' own allow rules.  In steady
# state on a host with hardening installed, no socket carries
# ``terok_socket_t`` and the broad allow rule was dead code.
#
# The broad ``container_t connectto terok_socket_t`` rule that this
# module used to ship was already inactive on hardened hosts (no
# socket carries the type once services switch to per-service types
# via ``setsockcreatecon()``).  Removing it makes the invariant
# explicit: containers must go through per-service typing on
# hardened hosts, full stop.  ``unconfined_t`` keeps full perms on
# the type for the service-side fallback in
# ``socket_selinux_context()`` ‚Äî when per-service types aren't loaded
# (e.g., terok_gate.te / terok_vault.te haven't been installed yet),
# services fall back to ``terok_socket_t`` and need to be able to
# create + bind + listen on it.  The container side, however, has no
# legitimate path to a ``terok_socket_t`` socket on hardened hosts.
#
# If you need the legacy container-connectto semantics back (e.g.,
# only ``terok_socket`` is loaded and ``terok_gate`` / ``terok_vault``
# are not), you can re-add the rule as a local module:
#
#     allow container_t terok_socket_t:unix_stream_socket connectto;
#
# Or, more sensibly: install the full hardening module set via
# ``terok hardening install``.
#
# Written in checkmodule-native module syntax (no refpolicy ``m4``
# macros), so the build path is ``checkmodule -M -m`` ‚Üí
# ``semodule_package`` ‚Üí ``semodule -i``.
#
# Install:  terok hardening install
# Remove:   terok hardening install --remove

require {
    type unconfined_t;
    class unix_stream_socket {
        create bind listen accept
        read write getattr getopt setopt shutdown
        connectto
    };
}

type terok_socket_t;

allow unconfined_t terok_socket_t:unix_stream_socket {
    create bind listen accept
    read write getattr getopt setopt shutdown
    connectto
};
